Kidnapped Japanese businessman NoboyukiWakaoji is alive and well and may soon be released, CardinalJaime Sin, the archbishop of Manila, said.    Wakaoji, head of the Philippines branch of Mitsui and CoLtd, is being visited on a daily basis by a senior priest, Sintold reporters at a briefing. He refused to reveal Wakaoji'swhereabouts.    The businessman was kidnapped last November and his captorshave demanded a five mln dlr ransom from Mitsui. REUTER&#3;